
# Testing

{{ project_name }} uses a layered testing strategy aligned with the clean / hexagonal
architecture.

## Running Tests

Tests run through **tox** with **pytest**:

```bash
task backend:test          # Run unit + property tests via tox
task backend:test:unit     # Run unit tests only
task backend:test:coverage # Run with coverage report
```

## Test Directory Structure

```
backend/tests/
+-- conftest.py            # Shared fixtures
+-- factories/             # Test data factories (factory_boy)
+-- fixtures/              # Reusable fixture data files
+-- utils/                 # Assertion helpers, fixture factories, mock builders
+-- unit/
|   +-- core/              # Domain entity and value object tests
|   +-- application/       # Service and use case tests
|   +-- adapters/          # Adapter tests (mocked I/O)
|   +-- ports/             # API route and CLI tests
{%- if api_style in ('graphql', 'both') %}
|   |   +-- test_graphql.py   # GraphQL schema, queries, mutations
{%- endif %}
|   +-- config/            # Config and settings tests
|   +-- utils/             # Utility function tests
+-- integration/
|   +-- test_api.py
|   +-- test_database.py
{%- if api_style in ('graphql', 'both') %}
|   +-- test_graphql_schema.py  # GraphQL schema integrity
{%- endif %}
+-- property/
|   +-- test_value_objects.py
|   +-- test_generate_registry.py
+-- performance/
    +-- (benchmarks)
```

## Test Commands

```bash
task backend:test              # Run all backend tests via tox
task backend:test:unit         # Unit tests only
task backend:test:integration  # Integration tests
task backend:test:property     # Property-based tests (Hypothesis)
task backend:test:performance  # Performance / benchmark tests
task backend:test:coverage     # Tests with coverage report
```

## Unit Tests

Test domain logic and use cases in isolation:

```python
from {{ project_slug }}.core.entities.user import User
from {{ project_slug }}.core.value_objects.email import Email


def test_create_user() -> None:
    email = Email("test@example.com")
    user = User(email=email, display_name="Test User")

    assert user.email == email
    assert user.display_name == "Test User"
```

## Integration Tests

Test the full HTTP request/response cycle:

```python
import pytest
from httpx import AsyncClient


@pytest.mark.anyio
async def test_health_endpoint(client: AsyncClient) -> None:
    response = await client.get("/health")

    assert response.status_code == 200
    assert response.json()["status"] == "healthy"
```

## Property-Based Tests

Use Hypothesis for property-based testing:

```python
from hypothesis import given, strategies as st
from {{ project_slug }}.core.value_objects.email import Email


@given(st.emails())
def test_valid_emails_accepted(email_str: str) -> None:
    email = Email(email_str)
    assert str(email) == email_str.lower().strip()
```

