The registry code generator has its own co-located test suite in `registry/tests/`:

```
registry/tests/
+-- conftest.py                         # Registry-specific fixtures
+-- test_generate_registry.py           # Unit tests for generator functions
+-- test_generate_registry_property.py  # Hypothesis property-based tests
```


```bash
task registry:test      # Unit + property tests for the generator
task registry:check     # CI gate — verify generated files are up-to-date
task registry:validate  # Validate naming_registry.json structure only
```

Registry tests verify:

- String helpers (`_to_pascal_case`, `_to_camel_case`) produce correct output
- Validation catches missing/invalid schema fields
- Python/TypeScript/env generation produces expected content
- Property-based invariants hold across random inputs (Hypothesis)


Performance tests live in `backend/tests/performance/` and use the `@pytest.mark.performance` marker:

```bash
task backend:test:performance   # Run performance tests
task test:performance           # Alias from root
```


| Level       | Speed   | Scope              | Where                      |
| ----------- | ------- | ------------------ | -------------------------- |
| Unit        | Fast    | Single function    | `backend/tests/unit/`      |
| Property    | Medium  | Invariant proofs   | `backend/tests/property/`  |
| Integration | Slow    | DB + HTTP paths    | `backend/tests/integration/`|
| Performance | Slow    | Benchmarks         | `backend/tests/performance/`|
| Registry    | Fast    | Generator logic    | `registry/tests/`          |
| Frontend    | Fast    | Components + utils | `frontend/tests/unit/`     |{% if use_playwright %}
| E2E         | Slowest | Full browser flow  | `frontend/tests/e2e/`      |{% endif %}
